The paper deals with combinatorial properties of proof nets in linear logic, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and mathematical logic. Specifically, it focuses on parallel cut elimination in multiplicative linear logic (MLL) proof nets and its application to the Taylor expansion of proof nets. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, such as Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Computer Science and Game Theory (cs.GT). However, given the emphasis on proof nets and their combinatorial properties, cs.LO and cs.PL seem to be the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also possible because they involve topics such as graph theory, optimization, and game theory, which are relevant to the paper.
